The center of the circle is O. So, $\triangle OCE$ and $\triangle OEC$ are both isosceles triangles with base angles $90^\circ - 12^\circ = 78^\circ$ and base angles $90^\circ - 24^\circ = 66^\circ$ respectively. \ $\$$The sum of angles in the triangle is $2(78^\circ) + \angle E = 36^\circ$. \ $\$$So, $ \ \angle E = 36^\circ$.



Let us draw the perpendicular line to the chord and call its point M.  The mirror of the radius goes through the midpoint of the chord, and divides the chord and the arc into equal parts. The because of the symmetry of the triangle, $\triangle OAE$ is congruent to $\triangle OME$. Thus, $IOE$ is 90.

\begin{align*} \angle AEO &=  \angle AOE -\angle E \\ &= 78 - 48 \\ &=30 \end{align*}

\begin{align*} \angle OME &= \angle E \\ &=30 \end{align*}

\begin{align*} 2\cos{\angle OME} &= - 2\sin{\angle AEO} \huge  \\ 2\cos{30^\circ} &=  \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \\ -2\sin{30^\circ} &= -1 \end{align*}

\begin{align*} \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} &= 1 \\ \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \cdot \frac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}} &= 1 \cdot \frac{\sqrt{3}}{\sqrt{3}} \\ \frac{3}{2\sqrt{3}} &= \frac{\sqrt{3}}{3}\end{align*}

$$\frac{2\sqrt{3}}{3}$$

